Package entities

Class Event

java.lang.Object
entities.Event
public class Event extends Object

This is just a placeholder class for storing Event entity when doing business logic code. Thus all properties are set to public.

This class behaves similarly to a struct in C. The purpose of this class is just for other outside functions to change its state, that's all. No methods, only attributes!

Author:
Nguyen Duc Thang

  • Constructor Details

    • Event

      public Event(int eventID, String eventName, String organizer, Instant startTime, Instant endTime, String location, String priority, List<String> participantsList, String remindBefore)

      This is a default constructor for making event class.

      Those JsonProperty are used for deserializing from JSON objects back to event object, because we have to send this Event object to client via JSON.

      Parameters:
      eventID - eventID of the event. Reminder: , again this class is just a placeholder, so sometimes we dont even need to specify this ID.
      eventName - Name of the event
      organizer - name of the organizer.
      startFrom - the time when the event will start. Reminder: when parsing JSON object into this Object, the date must follow this format YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.sZ
      endAt - the time when the event will end. Reminder: when parsing JSON object into this Object, the date must follow this format YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.sZ
      location - the location of the event. This can be any string, even a link to a Zoom meeting
      priority - priority of the event. Should be 1 these 3 strings: LOW,MEDIUM or HIGH. Throw an IllegalArgumentException if priority is anything else. case is not important
      participantsList - list of participants in the event. Reminder: this participantsList absolutely does not reflect the actual event list of the event.
      remindBefore - a string represent when the user wants to be reminded
